This paper proposes a neural machine translation model that focuses on enhancing source-side hierarchical representations using a bidirectional tree-based encoder. This is a common topic in the field of natural language processing, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The model also uses attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of sub-word level encoding to alleviate the out-of-vocabulary problem, which is a common issue in machine learning and natural language processing (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses empirical results to compare the proposed model to other neural translation models, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper may also fall under the category of computer vision (cs.CV) as it discusses the use of tree-based encoding.
